    <name>
      <text>Finding the Area of a Smaller Cone and the Slant Height of a Larger Cone from an Area Ratio</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The ratio of the area of two similar cones is \(\frac{{@square_list_a@}}{{@square_list_b@}}\).</p>
<p>(a). Find the area of the smaller cone if the area of the bigger cone is {@c@} \(\text{m}^2\). <b>Note:</b> Write your answer correct to <b>2 </b>decimal places.</p>
<p>[[input:ans1]] \(\text{m}^2\)[[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>(b). If the slanting height of the smaller cone is {@d@} m find the slanting height of the larger cone.<b>Note:</b> Write your answer correct to <b>2</b> decimal places.</p>
<p>[[input:ans2]] m[[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution<h3>
<p>\(\begin{align}\text{(a).Area of the smaller cone} = \frac{{@square_list_a@} \times {@c@}}{{@square_list_b@}}\\={@small_cone@}\\={@ta@}\end{align}\)</p>
<p> \(\begin{align}\text{(b).Slant height of the larger cone} = \frac{{@square_list_b@} \times {@d@}}{{@square_list_a@}}\\={@ta1@}\end{align}\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
